  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance for Cameroonese Returnees and Asylum-Seekers in N&apos;Djamena</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM in Chad has been tracking and monitoring complex mobility dimensions and providing humanitarian assistance to persons affected by forced displacement since 2014. Following the displacement of more than 80,000 persons from Kousseri, Cameroon to Chad due to deadly clashes between herders, fishermen and farmers, IOM in coordination with UNHCR and other humanitarian actors, is providing emergency assistance in the form of complete locally procured non-food item kits composed of non-food and hygiene items, kitchen sets, and emergency shelter items to meet the most urgent needs of the affected population.</narrative>
  </description>
